14/05/2006
DECANI, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- The town of Decani is a model of multiethnic democracy, UNMIK chief Soren Jessen-Petersen said during a visit Saturday (13 May).
Accompanied by Kosovo Prime Minister Agim Ceku, he held talks in the town with local leaders and citizens, praising their commitment to democracy and their readiness to work together.
The UNMIK head acknowledged the difficult economic situation in Decani, but voiced confidence that investments would start coming in once the Kosovo status issue is resolved.
(UN Web site - 13/05/06)
